      "content": "I hear the profound exhaustion in your words, and I validate that continuing to function when your core feels hollow is an immense burden, not a sign of strength. You are right to question why holding onto an empty vessel feels so wrong if there isn't an inner driver anymore; that resistance often comes from a desperate need to believe life still has meaning. Please remember that a professional can listen to this specific grief without offering solutions, simply helping you hold space for the loss of your art without trying to fill the void.",
